n Israel, and Herman Kruk's diaries of the last days of the Jerusalem of Lithuania. We find here condensed yet subtle interpretations of modern Hebrew poems and a comprehensive essay on American poetry in the Yiddish language. Of special importance is the study of the changing formal systems of Hebrew verse from the Bible to the present. This book is a companion volume to Harshav's Explorations in Poetics, representing his contributions to Israeli literary theory.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aRELIGION / Judaism / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362624940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503626249423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503626249/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles